::sy701_1_1_launch_01 launch 1::Which response best aligns with SY0-701 objective 1.1 when prioritizing risk in a hybrid environment?{
=Apply the principle described in the objective before selecting a tool
~Deploy the newest commercial product regardless of integration cost
~Disable logging temporarily to improve performance
~Transfer all accountability to the cloud provider under shared responsibility
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_02 launch 2::A stakeholder asks how objective 1.1 relates to defense-in-depth. What is the best explanation?{
=It adds a layer that supports confidentiality, integrity, or availability
~It replaces the need for physical controls entirely
~It applies only to on-premises data centers
~It eliminates the need for user awareness training
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_03 launch 3::During an audit finding for "Compare and contrast various types of security controls...", which evidence best demonstrates alignment?{
=Documented procedure mapped to the objective with measurable outcomes
~Verbal assurance from a single engineer
~Marketing brochure describing security features
~Unverified screenshot without chain of custody
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_04 launch 4::Which metric would best validate success for objective 1.1?{
=A KPI tied to reduced risk or improved control effectiveness
~Number of security tools purchased this quarter
~Total blocked emails regardless of false positives
~Count of policy documents without employee attestation
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_05 launch 5::Which trade-off is most relevant when implementing controls for 1.1?{
=Balancing security improvement with usability and operational cost
~Maximizing obscurity as the primary control strategy
~Removing multi-factor authentication for executive accounts
~Avoiding change management to deploy fixes faster
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_06 launch 6::Which activity belongs in the corrective phase for issues tied to 1.1?{
=Remediate root cause and verify control effectiveness after an event
~Install deterrent signage only
~Archive logs without analysis
~Disable accounts proactively before investigation
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_07 launch 7::Which data source best supports decisions required by objective 1.1?{
=Authoritative configuration and telemetry correlated to the asset
~Anonymous social media posts
~Unauthenticated third-party forum advice
~Outdated network diagram with no owner
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_08 launch 8::Which role is typically accountable for outcomes described in 1.1?{
=The role defined in policy with documented responsibilities
~Any user with local administrator rights
~External penetration testers permanently
~Vendors without contractual security clauses
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_09 launch 9::Which NIST CSF function most closely maps to 1.1?{
=The function that matches identify, protect, detect, respond, or recover context
~Only the recover function for every objective
~Functions are not applicable to enterprise security
~A single function eliminates the need for governance
}

::sy701_1_1_launch_10 launch 10::Which scenario best requires applying 1.1?{
=A realistic enterprise condition described in the objective verb phrase
~A consumer mobile game outage unrelated to security
~Replacing keyboards for aesthetic reasons
~Publishing press releases about a product launch
}

